\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sequana\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sequana\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sequana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sequana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(...) You will never find in me any desire to mock or denigrate.\", \"from\": 1218, \"to\": 1282, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I wanted to organise a ceremony that would repair and reconcile, and that would reaffirm the values of our Republic: liberty, equality and fraternity\\\".\", \"from\": 1283, \"to\": 1434, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The embassy said France was proud of its heritage and patrimony: it watched in horror as the cathedral of Notre-Dame in Paris burned down, and is following with emotion the stages of its reconstruction.\", \"from\": 1436, \"to\": 1638, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1453, \"end\": 1459, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.671965230993276, \"rank\": 0.4869620316605027, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 1556, \"end\": 1561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999560859588, \"rank\": 4.391392968810087e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France, it said, was also the country of free thought, secularism, the freedom to believe and the freedom not to believe.\", \"from\": 1640, \"to\": 1761, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1640, \"end\": 1646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.671965230993276, \"rank\": 0.4869620316605027, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As such, the country cherished the freedom of creation, the freedom that guided the opening ceremony of the Paris 2024 Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1762, \"to\": 1895, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can unsubscribe at any time by clicking the link in the footer of our emails.\", \"from\": 1897, \"to\": 1978, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We useMailchimpas our marketing platform.\", \"from\": 1979, \"to\": 2020, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By                     subscribing, you acknowledge that your information will be transferred to Mailchimp for processing.\", \"from\": 2021, \"to\": 2143, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To view comments, please register for free or log in to your account.\", \"from\": 2145, \"to\": 2214, \"entities\": []}]}"